      "content": "you say \"don't get lost in it,\" but what if being lost is the only place that feels real? being \"in it\" is the only way i can even feel close to him anymore. everything else is just pretending. it feels like i'm just waiting for something to end so i can finally stop this exhausting act of pretending to be alive. does it ever actually get better, or do people just get better at lying to themselves?",
